					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6011177#post-3816405</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6011177/scp-3362#post-3816405</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 29 May 2018 02:40:09 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Gilphon</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3629097</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Man, this doomsday gets more ridiculous with every article and I love it.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;spoiler</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Close</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>So now we have Seagulls, Shark-punchers and a robot working together to find Yahweh's collection of old Christmas movies in order to save humanity.</p> <p>And it occurred to me as I was writing this comment that if they don't find it before June 10th, Yahweh will be gone for good and the doomsday will probably escalate in some esoteric and unpredictable way.</p> <p>Though even if they find it, they're still gonna have figure out who or what 3362 counts as Yahweh's superior.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
