					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6011177#post-3815413</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6011177/scp-3362#post-3815413</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 28 May 2018 03:52:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zzuxon</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1496981</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Ok, so I find the concept of this brilliant. It's so strange and out there. I love skips where it has some sort of rule (In this case, preferring christmas movies) that you don't entirely understand, but their presence suggests some sort of broader internal logic. I think this makes an interesting concept a lot more interesting. But then&#8230;</p> <blockquote> <p>Recovered data files show that O5-10 was a devout Catholic.</p> </blockquote> <p>Holy crap what a wham line.</p> <p>My only criticism is that the connection to the Migration scenario seems shoehorned in&#8230; unless&#8230;<br /> In the process of writing this comment I had a realization.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Collapsible&nbsp;for&nbsp;dramatic&nbsp;effect</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Close</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>Am I meant to believe the bird god was able to cause the doomsday event because Yahweh is trapped in an old Christmas movie?</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
